[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    192[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mEvent-normalizer Lambda fails on a malformed message[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m (the EHR emits an unexpected HL7 segment, the formulary crosswalk is stale and the lookup fails, the dose-string parser hits an edge case). Lambda's default async retry behavior is two retries over six hours and then drop. The dispense event is silently lost: no anomaly check happens, the pharmacist sees no flag (because there was no flag to send), and the pipeline has no signal that a check was missed.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    193[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mReal-time-anomaly-service Lambda fails during cache lookup or rule evaluation[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m (DynamoDB throttle, Feature Store cold-cache miss timeout, S3 read on the rule library timeouts). Same retry-then-drop pattern. The dispense event passes through unscored. For a patient-safety system this is the failure mode the entire pipeline is designed to prevent: a dispense without an anomaly check is exactly the case the system is supposed to catch.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    194[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFeedback-capture Lambda fails on a malformed event[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m (the analyst tooling emits an unexpected disposition value, the anomaly_event_id references a record not in OpenSearch due to retention rotation, the ADE event has a date format the parser doesn't handle). The label is never written, the OpenSearch record stays "open" forever, the missed-adverse-event signal that the recipe's Honest Take identifies as critical is silently lost.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    195[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    196[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mWithout DLQs, these failures appear only in CloudWatch Logs and require log-trawling to discover. For a system whose value proposition is catching the failures clinicians don't catch, silently-failing scoring is the worst possible failure mode.[K
