[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    198[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mThe recipe's Variations section mentions "graceful degradation" as a discipline but doesn't connect it to DLQs. The Disaster Recovery paragraph says "The rules layer should be deployable as a standalone fallback even if the ML components are unavailable," which is the right discipline at a different abstraction level (degraded-mode operation) but doesn't address the per-event poison-message recovery.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    199[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Add to the Architecture Diagram three SQS DLQs: [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mevent-normalizer-dlq[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mreal-time-anomaly-service-dlq[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m, and [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mfeedback-capture-dlq[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m. Add a Prerequisites note: "Configure each Lambda's [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mOnFailure[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m destination to a dedicated SQS DLQ. CloudWatch alarms on DLQ depth alert the on-call clinical-informatics and pharmacy-operations teams; for the real-time-anomaly-service DLQ specifically, alarm threshold should be 1 (a single dropped dispense event is a patient-safety event). Replay events from DLQ after fixing the root cause; for events older than the dispense window (typically 1 hour), escalate to clinical-informatics review rather than auto-replay because the dispense decision has already been made." Add a "DLQ and replay" bullet to "Why This Isn't Production-Ready" that ties the discipline to the existing graceful-degradation discussion. Cross-link to the existing "Graceful degradation when dependencies fail" bullet.[K
