[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    210[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m2[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mGranularity.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Is the suppression at the patient level ("suppress all dose anomalies for this patient because they're on chemo"), at the drug level ("suppress dose anomalies for cytotoxic drugs only"), or at the protocol level ("suppress dose anomalies for drugs in this specific protocol's regimen")? The latter is the safest (won't over-suppress); the former is the easiest to implement; the middle is the operational compromise. The recipe doesn't say.[K
