[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    546[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mCoordinate with the existing code review ([38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mreviews/chapter03.04-code-review.md[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m). The code review PASSed-with-reservations on three WARNINGs and seven NOTEs in the Python companion. WARNING 1 (broken [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140m__name__ != "__production__"[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m assert) has now appeared in all four Chapter 3 Python companions; treat it as the single-cookbook-wide-fix candidate. WARNING 2 (S3 [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mput_object[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m without [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mSSEKMSKeyId[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m) parallels Recipes 3.1, 3.2, 3.3. WARNING 3 ([38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mtotal_dose_mg_equiv[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m feature mixing incompatible units) is recipe-3.4-specific and Python-companion-only (the main recipe pseudocode doesn't show a feature-engineering example). The code review's Finding 8 ([38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mon_pharmacist_response[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m skips the OpenSearch anomaly-record update) is downstream-related to A1 in this expert review and should be addressed in the same editorial pass: when the idempotency guard is added, the OpenSearch update should also be implemented.[K
